Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Trim the @aubergine{1}, then cut
into roughly 2cm pieces.

Pop the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g} onto a piece of foil with a drizzle of
@oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fold the foil, sealing on all sides
to create a parcel.

Put the aubergine onto a large #baking tray{}. Add a generous drizzle of oil,
season, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. Place the tomato
parcel alongside.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until soft and golden,
~{17-18%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, tear the @ciabatta{1} into roughly 2cm chunks and pop onto another
baking tray. Drizzle with oil and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Bake on the middle shelf of the oven until golden, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Once golden, remove from the oven and set aside.

While the croutons bake, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated)
(or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain and rinse the @lentils{1%carton} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a medium #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the @bacon lardons{90%g}. Stir-fry until golden,
~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Add the lentils to the pan and stir together until piping hot,
~{1-2%minutes}. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then remove from the
heat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon
> thoroughly.

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @balsamic glaze{12%ml}, @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g},
@sugar{1%tsp} and @olive oil{1.5%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

When ready, add the bacon, lentils, roasted aubergine and tomatoes to the
dressing and toss to coat.

Allow to sit for ~{1%minute} to absorb the flavours.

Just before serving, mix the @baby leaf mix{50%g} and croutons into your salad,
then share between your #bowls{}.

Crumble the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g} over the top and drizzle with the
@Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g}.

Enjoy!